@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

participant "Driver" as Driver
participant "Process" as Process
participant "Timeout" as Timeout

note over Driver
The driver can be a test
or a main loop.
end note

note over Timeout
Timeouts advance only
when Process.tick() is called.
end note

' [step1 {"name":"Register Timeout"}]
Process -> Timeout : start timeout(3 ticks)
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Tick 1"}]
Driver -> Process : tick()
Process -> Timeout : tick()
Timeout -> Timeout : remaining = 2
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Tick 2"}]
Driver -> Process : tick()
Process -> Timeout : tick()
Timeout -> Timeout : remaining = 1
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"Tick 3"}]
Driver -> Process : tick()
Process -> Timeout : tick()
Timeout -> Timeout : remaining = 0
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"Timeout Fires"}]
Process --> Timeout : isFired()
Process -> Process : handle timeout error
note over Process
On timeout the process can either return
error response to client or do 
operations like re-election, marking nodes
as down etc.
end note
' [/step5]

note over Process, Timeout
Time does not advance on its own.
The timeout fires only after enough explicit ticks.
end note

@enduml
